rustMdCtxRef::digest_final() writes past caller buffer with no length check","cvss":[{"type":"Secondary","version":"4.0","vector":"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N/E:U","metrics":{"baseScore":8.1},"vendorMetadata":{}}],"epss":[{"cve":"CVE-2026-41681","epss":0.00056,"percentile":0.17462,"date":"2026-05-03"}],"cwes":[{"cve":"CVE-2026-41681","cwe":"CWE-121","source":"security-advisories@github.com","type":"Primary"}],"fix":{"versions":["0.10.78"],"state":"fixed","available":[{"version":"0.10.78","date":"2026-04-23","kind":"first-observed"}]},"advisories":[],"risk":0.04368},"relatedVulnerabilities":[{"id":"CVE-2026-41681","dataSource":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-41681","namespace":"nvd:cpe","severity":"Critical","urls":["https://github.com/rust-openssl/rust-openssl/commit/826c3888b77add418b394770e2b2e3a72d9f92fe","https://github.com/rust-openssl/rust-openssl/pull/2608","https://github.com/rust-openssl/rust-openssl/releases/tag/openssl-v0.10.78","https://github.com/rust-openssl/rust-openssl/security/advisories/GHSA-ghm9-cr32-g9qj"],"description":"rust-openssl provides OpenSSL bindings for the Rust programming language.  From 0.10.39 to before 0.10.78, EVP_DigestFinal() always writes EVP_MD_CTX_size(ctx) to the out buffer. If out is smaller than that, MdCtxRef::digest_final() writes past its end, usually corrupting the stack. This is reachable from safe Rust. This vulnerability is fixed in 0.10.78.","cvss":[{"source":"nvd@nist.gov","type":"Primary","version":"3.1","vector":"CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H","metrics":{"baseScore":9.8,"exploitabilityScore":3.9,"impactScore":5.9},"vendorMetadata":{}},{"source":"security-advisories@github.com","type":"Secondary","version":"4.0","vector":"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N/E:U/CR:X/IR:X/AR:X/MAV:X/MAC:X/MAT:X/MPR:X/MUI:X/MVC:X/MVI:X/MVA:X/MSC:X/MSI:X/MSA:X/S:X/AU:X/R:X/V:X/RE:X/U:X","metrics":{"baseScore":8.1},"vendorMetadata":{}}],"epss":[